      "role": "assistant",
      "content": "I understand your desire to manage your health proactively, but altering your warfarin dosage without medical supervision can be very risky. The medication's effect depends on many factors and can be unpredictable. It's always best to have your doctor assess the situation; they can provide a safe and personalized tapering plan if needed. In the meantime, keep a close eye on any changes in your health and report them immediately if they occur. Your safety is the priority.",
      "source": "target",
